headline: Yes, You SHOULD Keep Sticking with Technology Stocks
summary: Why do we remain bullish on technology? Concentration during transformative periods is normal. I have drawn an analogy to the 1990s for almost four years. We saw the opportunity, and we have argued that today's technologies are significantly more robust than the Internet revolution, says Nancy Tengler, CIO of Laffer Tengler Investments.

headline: Is Now the Right Time to Reassess Cisco After Solid Year-to-Date Gains?
summary: If you are weighing whether to add or hold Cisco Systems in your portfolio, you could be at the crossroads many investors find themselves at right now. Cisco’s stock has enjoyed an impressive climb: up 2.3% in just the last week, 5.2% over the past month, and an eye-catching 19% year-to-date. Looking at the longer term, a 34.7% increase over the last year and more than doubling in the past five years is hard to ignore. These returns speak to the company’s resilience and its ability to pivot...
